          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "One day he asked me, ‚ÄúWhy does he dress like a girl?‚Äù ‚Äî no direct disapproval, but it‚Äôs in the subtext. At this point in my life, I wanted to be like K-pop stars and their fans. I would try to stylize myself like the stars. (Whenever I‚Äôd come back from the barber, my parents would always be confused as to why I didn‚Äôt cut my hair shorter.) I learned the dances, to which my parents were supportive. But I don‚Äôt think Chris Pang‚Äôs body would resolve the tensions between father and K-pop sons."
          },
