          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "<i>Lilting</i> suddenly comes to mind. When I first saw the film, I didn‚Äôt know what to think of it. I was only looking at it through the narrow lens of race and cultural differences. I formed some shallow thoughts about the language barriers, and how some messages were lost in translation. It wasn‚Äôt until I reached this point in my writing that I realized the careful messaging about masculinity and fluidity. In his thesis thesis ‚ÄúConstructing a New Asian Masculinity: Reading <i>Lilting</i> Against Other Films by Asian Filmmakers‚Äù<cite>Cheng</cite>, Feng Cheng writes of <i>Lilting</i> that:"
